# Prompt: Implement a Complete Analytics Platform for phung.work (Google Analytics 4 + Microsoft Clarity + PostHog)
## Objective
Implement a complete, production-ready analytics platform for **phung.work** that combines:
* Google Analytics 4 (GA4)
* Microsoft Clarity
* PostHog
The implementation must be **modular**, **privacy-first**, **provider-agnostic**, and designed to support additional analytics providers in the future (Cloudflare Analytics, Plausible, Umami, Mixpanel, etc.) without modifying business logic.
The analytics system should become a shared infrastructure used by every tool across the website.
Do not directly call `gtag`, `clarity`, or `posthog` from application pages or components. All analytics must go through a centralized Analytics Manager.
---
# Objectives
The platform should answer questions such as:
* Which tools are opened the most?
* Which tools are actually used?
* Which tools are abandoned before processing?
* Which tools are downloaded the most?
* Which categories are most popular?
* Which searches return no results?
* Which browsers or devices have the highest error rate?
* Which pages have the highest bounce rate?
* Which tools should appear in "Popular Tools"?
* Which tools should be recommended together?
* Which features are rarely used?
The system should support product analytics, SEO analytics, UX analytics, and performance analytics.
---
# Architecture
Create a dedicated analytics module.
```text
src/
 ├── analytics/
 │
 ├── core/
 │      AnalyticsManager.ts
 │      AnalyticsProvider.ts
 │      EventQueue.ts
 │      ConsentManager.ts
 │      SessionManager.ts
 │      UserProperties.ts
 │      EventBuilder.ts
 │
 ├── providers/
 │      GoogleAnalyticsProvider.ts
 │      MicrosoftClarityProvider.ts
 │      PostHogProvider.ts
 │
 ├── hooks/
 │      useAnalytics.ts
 │      useTrackPage.ts
 │      useTrackTool.ts
 │      useTrackSearch.ts
 │      useTrackFavorite.ts
 │      useTrackDownload.ts
 │
 ├── events/
 │      page.ts
 │      tool.ts
 │      search.ts
 │      download.ts
 │      favorite.ts
 │      upload.ts
 │      error.ts
 │      performance.ts
 │
 ├── types/
 ├── constants/
 ├── utils/
 └── index.ts
```
Business code must never communicate directly with GA4, Clarity, or PostHog.
Everything goes through AnalyticsManager.
